Data Providers:-

1]They are used to provide the data to the test methods in TestNG.

2]Using Data provider we can can easily inject multiple values into the same test case.

3]It comes in-built in TestNG framework & popularly used in data driven frameworks.

SYNTAX

@DataProvider(name="name of DP")
public Object[][] dataProvider(){

return new Object[][]{values}

}

* DataProvider annotation has only single attribute that is "name".

* DataProvider are separate methods used in test functions,this annotation is not used on test function like testNG parameters.

*DataProvider returns a 2D list of Objects.

*In case you don't define name of DataProvider method , DataProvider method name is considers it's default name.